Or you can do away with the lame C++ language and use ocaml. Please look at 
the list archives for the example of an imperative graph module I posted.

You could also implement a functional "map" but I don't think you would be 
happy writing an algorithm like subgraph isomorphism with such a thing... 
Look at the caml humps there is such a functional graph impl. there.

As for drawing, you'll prolly have to stick with one of the free graph drawing 
tools.

